sentences: He started as a musician in the late 1970s as a member of the jazz rock/jazz fusion band, Kittyhawk.

He later appeared on the majority of the tracks on the group's follow-up album, Reel Life, including their most successful single, "Waiting for a Star to Fall," on which he is featured as one of two drummers.
He also played drums in Jackson Browne's World in Motion and toured with him for over four years.
He played 2nd percussion and donned a pig mask during the See You on the Other Side and Family Values 2006 tours, as well as their MTV: Unplugged performance.
Jochum left the back-up band shortly after Korn's 2007 European Tour, due to setlist changes that did not involve Jochum's drumming.
Jochum returned to the Korn world in November 2007 following Joey Jordison's return to Slipknot.
He was back out of the band in 2008, replaced by Ray Luzier for Korn's early 2008 European tour.
